<paragraph id="8BF936F7FF9D7A376CB2792DFC5CF45F" blockId="10.[192,802,1855,1909]" lastBlockId="10.[830,1440,199,529]" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">
AFFINITIES. The described features distinguish 
<taxonomicName id="4C464D74FF9D7A376EB9792DFF16F13B" authority="Kovařík, 2012" authorityName="Kovařík" authorityYear="2012" class="Arachnida" family="Chaerilidae" genus="Chaerilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="10" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="solegladi" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B932EAE5FF9D7A376EB9792DFF16F13B" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">C. solegladi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B932EAE5FF9D7A376C8C794CFEDAF13B" bold="true" box="[254,315,1886,1909]" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A201579EFF9D7A376C8C794CFEDAF13B" box="[254,315,1886,1909]" pageId="10" pageNumber="9" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
from all other species of the genus. They are recounted in the key. The female of 
<taxonomicName id="4C464D74FF9D7A3768B17ED5FAA5F690" authority="Kovařík, 2012" authorityName="Kovařík" authorityYear="2012" box="[1219,1348,199,222]" class="Arachnida" family="Chaerilidae" genus="Chaerilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="10" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="solegladi" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B932EAE5FF9D7A3768B17ED5FAA5F690" box="[1219,1348,199,222]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">C. solegladi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B932EAE5FF9D7A3769397ED5FA66F690" bold="true" box="[1355,1415,199,222]" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A201579EFF9D7A3769397ED5FA66F690" box="[1355,1415,199,222]" pageId="10" pageNumber="9" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C464D74FF9D7A376F937EF4FB9AF6B3" authorityName="Pocock" authorityYear="1899" box="[993,1147,230,253]" class="Arachnida" family="Chaerilidae" genus="Chaerilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="10" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laevimanus">
<emphasis id="B932EAE5FF9D7A376F937EF4FB9AF6B3" box="[993,1147,230,253]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">C. laevimanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but the males of these two species are quite different. Whereas the male of 
<taxonomicName id="4C464D74FF9D7A3769397F16FC6AF774" authorityName="Pocock" authorityYear="1899" class="Arachnida" family="Chaerilidae" genus="Chaerilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="10" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laevimanus">
<emphasis id="B932EAE5FF9D7A3769397F16FC6AF774" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">C. laevimanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has longer and narower chela of pedipalps, the male of 
<taxonomicName id="4C464D74FF9D7A376FEA7F50FBF8F717" authority="Kovařík, 2012" authorityName="Kovařík" authorityYear="2012" box="[920,1049,322,345]" class="Arachnida" family="Chaerilidae" genus="Chaerilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="10" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="solegladi" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B932EAE5FF9D7A376FEA7F50FBF8F717" box="[920,1049,322,345]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">C. solegladi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B932EAE5FF9D7A3768537F50FBBCF717" bold="true" box="[1057,1117,322,345]" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A201579EFF9D7A3768537F50FBBCF717" box="[1057,1117,322,345]" pageId="10" pageNumber="9" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
has the chela robust (
<figureCitation id="137D2A72FF9D7A3769387F50FA79F717" box="[1354,1432,322,345]" captionStart="Figures 34–47" captionStartId="9.[192,278,1838,1861]" captionTargetBox="[195,1437,173,1788]" captionTargetId="figure-6@9.[192,1440,168,1808]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figures 34–47: Chaerilus solegladi Kovařík, sp. n.. 34–44. Dorsal (34) and ventral (35) views, movable finger (36), second metasomal segment lateral (37), and trichobothrial pattern of pedipalp (38–45), ♂ (45 mm) holotype. 46–47. Dorsal (46) and ventral (47) views, ♀ (42 mm) allotype." pageId="10" pageNumber="9">Fig. 38</figureCitation>
) like the male of 
<taxonomicName id="4C464D74FF9D7A37687F7F72FB44F739" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1880" box="[1037,1189,352,375]" class="Arachnida" family="Chaerilidae" genus="Chaerilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="10" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="variegatus">
<emphasis id="B932EAE5FF9D7A37687F7F72FB44F739" box="[1037,1189,352,375]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">C. variegatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, these two species cannot be confused, because 
<taxonomicName id="4C464D74FF9D7A3768AC7F6DFA93F7D8" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1880" box="[1246,1394,383,406]" class="Arachnida" family="Chaerilidae" genus="Chaerilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="10" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="variegatus">
<emphasis id="B932EAE5FF9D7A3768AC7F6DFA93F7D8" box="[1246,1394,383,406]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">C. variegatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the movable finger of pedipalp with 13–15 cutting edges composed of granules, whereas 
<taxonomicName id="4C464D74FF9D7A3768D17FAEFAC9F79D" authority="Kovařík, 2012" authorityName="Kovařík" authorityYear="2012" box="[1187,1320,444,467]" class="Arachnida" family="Chaerilidae" genus="Chaerilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="10" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="solegladi" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B932EAE5FF9D7A3768D17FAEFAC9F79D" box="[1187,1320,444,467]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">C. solegladi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B932EAE5FF9D7A3769407FAEFA93F79D" bold="true" box="[1330,1394,444,467]" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A201579EFF9D7A3769407FAEFA93F79D" box="[1330,1394,444,467]" pageId="10" pageNumber="9" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
has the movable finger with 7 or 8 cutting edges composed of granules.
</paragraph>
